President Obama released a statement expressing his support for the USA FREEDOM Act, which aims to protect the privacy and civil liberties of American citizens while also ensuring national security. He welcomes the Senate's passage of the bill and promises to sign it when it reaches his desk. The President emphasizes that the legislation will strengthen civil liberty safeguards and increase public confidence in national security programs. He also applauds the efforts of specific members of Congress who played a significant role in passing this bipartisan achievement.